Repository-level rules for the Windsurf agent.

Same content as .cursorrules / CLAUDE.md / AGENTS.md / GEMINI.md / .github/copilot-instructions.md — kept in sync for cross-harness portability.

On every prompt:
- Read STATE.md and the current BACKLOG.md item before suggesting code.
- Follow the master skill stack at /Volumes/hex/current-work/skills/ — see .claude/SKILLS_REFERENCE.md.
- Read the matching skill before non-trivial work.

Hard rules:
- Author = cyfen-code <code@cyfen.co>.
- License = BSD-3-Clause.
- TDD: failing test first.
- Smoke gate before feature work.
- Threat-model gate for trust-boundary changes.
- No secrets in source / logs / errors.
- Local-first AI default.
- Compile-time security where possible.
- Defense in depth — ≥2 independent controls per high-impact threat.
- Refactors must preserve current product behaviour; additive where possible.

Compaction:
- Before compaction: dump task / questions / next 3 steps to STATE.md.
- After resume: re-read STATE.md + BACKLOG + last 3 PROGRESS entries before action.
